      <title>Anguish and tier 1 BP click effects, why the not short duration buff window?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=259563#M259563</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I don't know if anyone else has complained about this, but I think it doesn't make much sense for the click effects on the BPs to take up a buff slot when they only last for 24 seconds. The short duration buff window was made for things that don't last long right? Epic 1.5s and 2.0s came from the same expansion and their effects last longer than the BP clicks and they still go to the short one. With 21 buff slots not really being enough in the end game from lots of important spells being used taking up many slots, it would help people out a lot by moving those buffs to the window they belong instead of wasting a slot or having to click something else off for 24 seconds. Granted, some of the clicks are more useful than others&amp;nbsp;and some people don't even use them, but the post is not about the usefulness.&amp;nbsp;I can't be the only one that thinks this is lame, feedback please!&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
