    <item>
      <title>Record Keeping in EQ</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=259555#M259555</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Would like to start by saying this is *not* a rant against CS. While it involves them its more the Quality of the behind the scene records kept by the game, or lack thereof&amp;nbsp;that concerns me and drives me to post this.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I fully accept the dessision they made that was made with the facts they had available to them.. but what I would like to bring into Question, with some concern,&amp;nbsp;is the poor Quality of Transaction and Record keeping available to them to make their decisions&amp;nbsp;.. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;For years I have thought that every transaction or exchange made between Players and or NPC's&amp;nbsp;was kept on a Database as a useful tool for catching cheaters and or resolving CS issues, but the events of the other night revealed to me that this was not the case and in fact the Records they do have&amp;nbsp;seem to be&amp;nbsp;prone to errors...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What happened was on the Combine Server I had bought 2 "Golden Fire Wedding rings" with my druid in EC, I then ported to Stonebrunt to give them to my SK on my second account, but in my hurry I handed them to her pet rather than trading them to her... I fully accept that this was my fault. After I slapped myself around a bit someone in the group said I could petition to get things back that I had accidentally handed to a pet. So I figure might as well try... on a regular server it would have been no big deal, but on the Combine the Rings almost cost me all my money.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Happily within a hour I got a response from a GM... I was a bit surprised when he asked for more details, he said he was having trouble finding the transaction. I tried to pinpoint the exact time of the transactions for him (I had bought the rings only a few minutes before I handed them to the pet, and petitioned within a minute or two of the trade) &amp;nbsp;I also&amp;nbsp;pointed out the pet was still up and if he could inspect it the pet should still be wearing them. I got no further response that night and finely logged.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The Next day I had another response from a different GM who also stated he still could not find either the transaction in their records.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;No record of &amp;nbsp;me purchasing the rings in EC or me handing to the pet minutes later existed on their Database despite the fact I could pinpoint the times for both transactions to within a minute for them.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But what *really* surprised me was when he stated&amp;nbsp;he had checked my Character back two month's and could only find a Transaction on June 16th where my Druid had bought a ring from a player then sold it to a vendor.... but....I'm playing on the Combine... it came up live on June 28th....how could they have records of my character making transactions&amp;nbsp;12&amp;nbsp;days before the server or my character existed. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Things that make you go Hmmm.....&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Jul 2006 14:24:22 GMT</pubDate>
