    <item>
      <title>Has the time come for INT caster disciplines?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=259304#M259304</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've been following the caster "plight" for some time, and the more I think about this, the more I'm starting to believe that the time has come for casters of all types to gain a series of disciplines which appears to me the only real way to address *some* of their issues (note: not all, but a good amount).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The issues I've seen personally (As a tank and as a Necro) while they're not as in touch with DD casters, I've seen enough of them to at least form a rudimentary set of ideas that may help (or may not help but rather just be a set of ramblings).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Several issues surrounding casters are&amp;nbsp;as follows:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Burst DPS&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Survival in case of an "oopsie"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Burst Aggro Reduction&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Pet Value on raids, perceived and real&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Many of these weaknesses can be addressed via discipline, rather than a mudflation of spells, a set of caster disciplines for each class could in theory be created that allows these issues to be addressed in a reasonable and flexible&amp;nbsp;way without interfering with other game mechanics nearly as much, and in such a way that addresses other areas of play which are affected by casting restrictions (Cast times, mana, etc).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A couple of Examples:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Burst defense:&amp;nbsp; A rune which absorbs say...50k damage,&amp;nbsp; increase channelling to absurd levels,&amp;nbsp; with a&amp;nbsp;6 second duration, reuse of 40 minutes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; This would allow a caster to potentially survive a case of overaggro every so often, certainly not making a habit out of it, but not making them suffer instant splattage guaranteed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Aggro Dropping:&amp;nbsp; A discipline that when invoked, the next time Invisibility is cast, drops the caster WAY down the hatelist of the NPC.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 10 minute reuse.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- "Jaboner, get this thing off of me"... Essentially a guaranteed taunt for your pet at your command&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Pet disciplines which nearly match melee disciplines /pet mightystrike... /pet evasive... Since pets don't do a very good job of keeping up with mudflation, giving them the ability to serve a burst DPS function would be cool, and giving them a smaller than melee, yet reasonable chance to survive an otherwise untenable situation.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Burst DPS:&amp;nbsp; You know the drill... something simple like making all spells that land, crit for 1 minute... another variant is "Make all spells that are cast for the next 45 seconds always land for full", or other type of stuff.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- An Enchanter one that ensures that ANY mezzable NPC for the next 30 seconds becomes mezzed if they hit the enchanter, refresh time 40 minutes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There's a billion other things I can think of, but you get the idea.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What this would do for the game is 3 fold, it addresses some of the current outstanding caster damage balance issues, it addresses survival/mitigation issues, and it does so in such a way that gives flexibility and choices to said casters.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
